<br>
If the powers that be dictate that magicians must have a stupid summoned only crowd control, then give be <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> ROOT SUMMONED</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
Now what mage has not wanted to play with their own root at some time, eh?<br>
<br>
Root Summoned, call it <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hold Elements</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or something, would be much more consistant for the mage class, be about as useful as mezz summoned, and most importantly: would be fun for mages to play with.<br>
<br>
As for the nuke issue, well, I am deferring judgment here.<br>
<br>
First, it is true that all caster classes need to deal <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>adequate</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> damage, usually through nukes, in order to participate beyond the required number for support on raids.  Excess support yields diminishing returns, while extra damages adds directly.<br>
<br>
Second, if by the above criteria, a class has been sub-par, inadequate damage dealers, then they should see a relatively larger upgrade in their damage dealing capacity than classes that are already adequate damage dealers.  The proposed spells reflect this trend.<br>
<br>
Finally, pets in general and mage pets in specific have received tremendous upgrades of late.  They are useable in a much greater variety of circumstances, and are much more effective at dealing damage than they were before.  Of all the caster classes, except possibly necros, we are the most independent of nukes as a source of dealing damage.<br>
<br>
Given that, it is not at all surprising to see the relative advantage of our nukes fade as others improve.<br>
<br>
Since our utility is rather narrow, and damage dealing remains the primary function of the magician class, we must ensure that pets plus nukes together deals substantially more damage than almost any other caster class, and significantly more than any caster whose primary function is support.<br>
<br>
Without seeing the pets, it is hard to evaluate the worth of the proposed nukes.<br>
<br>
